PROGRAM:

import java.util.Scanner;
public class grade {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        System.out.println("Enter your mark: ");
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int mark = sc.nextInt();
        if(mark>=90 && mark<=100){
            System.out.println("grade is 'A'");
        }
        else if(mark >= 80){
            System.out.println("grade is 'B'");
        }
        else if(mark >=70){
            System.out.println("grade is:'C'");
        }
        else if(mark >= 60){
            System.out.println("grade is 'D'");
        }
        else if(mark >=50){
            System.out.println("grade is 'E'");
        }
        else if(mark >=0){
            System.out.println("grade is 'F'");
        }
        else{
            System.out.println("Invalid Input! please enter your mark between 0 to 100.");
        }
        }
        }


OUTPUT:
Enter your mark: 
96
grade is 'A'
Enter your mark: 
85
grade is 'B'


DESCRIPTION:
This is a simple program to calculate the grade for your mark.
the condition has been checked and the grade for the appropriate entered mark has been printed.
